column1: We're having a snowflake contest! Make a space-themed snowflake (or garland) and win prizes! Details: http://bit.ly/gWhJI9
Scale solar system: if the Sun were at the top of your head and Pluto at your feet  then Uranus would be right where expected. Really.

App-y New Year. Here's an extensive catalog of astronomy apps for your mobile devices. Thanks to Andrew Fraknoi!   http://t.co/7FDi62M2
Happy anniversary  Oppy! Warrantied for 90 days  the rover starts 9th year on Mars with new investigation: http://t.co/WwCPd2KB
Venus- brilliant in the west early evening. Jupiter- higher in the southwest. Stars twinkle  planets don't. See 'em @ChabotSpace
SKA Board has received the SSAC's site evaluation report and recommendation - see SKA on Facebook for more details.
Like rocket launches  how about 5? Tonight!!! Yes  you'll have to go outside (if you live on the central East Coast US) http://t.co/SBblyEus

Teleconference on future NASA Mars exploration at 1pm EDT. You can listen at: http://t.co/zRcHZIm9

I'll be on NPR Science Friday today at 2-230p (EDT). Listen in as I talk about NASA science and Space Exploration.
On the road again! Oppy drives for the first time after 130 sols at her winter parking spot  http://t.co/xBPLfxEU
SpaceX had a pad abort. Simple reality of such complex operations. I'm happy to see the rocket sitting safely on the pad following an abort.
SKA members meeting now underway in Amsterdam.
Dual site agreed for Square Kilometre Array telescope.
#Dragon has attached with the International Space Station!!!! History has been made!!!
Great SKA article in The Economist http://t.co/X0duIPsO
First picture of #Dragon in the ocean as it awaits recovery. http://t.co/sEtwNqag
I love the smell of the universe in the morning.
The SKA Organisation is now recruiting: http://t.co/F4wJovlk
You've come a long way  Oppy! Today  this @NASA Mars rover celebrates 3 000 sols of operation on the Red Planet.
On the day we reserve to tell ourselves America is great - July 4 - Europe reminds us that we suck at science. #HiggsBoson
This Mars panorama is the next best thing to being there. 817 pics from Oppy stitched into one 360º view: http://t.co/S4DMexic
Does it disturb anyone else that "The Los Angeles Angels" baseball team translates directly to "The The Angels Angels"?
Correction! Gold can only be formed in the supernova death of a massive star; any gold on Earth was formed before our solar system existed!
follow the Mars Curiosity lander at @MarsCuriosity  20 days until landing on Mars.
This is HOT: NASA SUCCESSFULLY TESTS HYPERSONIC INFLATABLE HEAT SHIELD  http://t.co/QjoRTflP
SATELLITES SEE UNPRECEDENTED GREENLAND ICE SHEET SURFACE MELT. http://t.co/AjLJl17b
Just an FYI:  If you removed all veins  arteries  & capillaries from your body and laid them end to end  you will die.
6 days until Mars Science Laboratory (MSL) landing on Mars!  Check  http://t.co/RRNNF6Cf for events in your area.  Go Curiosity!  #STEM
I'm often asked whether I believe in Global Warming.  I now just reply with the question: "Do you believe in Gravity?"
Breaking news:  I've been invited to talk about Mars Science Laboratory to Colbert Nation tonight!!!
Watch me tonight on The Colbert Report at 11:30 PM EST on Comedy Central to discuss NASA  and Curiosity!! http://t.co/cgMuS9Av
Colbert show talking about Mars tonight.  THAT WAS FUN!!!   Now the hard job of landing on Mars. http://t.co/cgMuS9Av
I'm less than 500 000 miles from Mars & the Red Planet looks about the size as a full moon seen from Earth. 2 days to landing!
When I land on Mars  it'll be 5:31 UTC Aug. 6. See this handy chart for conversion to your time zone: http://t.co/7zJ6Z2vw
The day we stop exploring is the day we commit ourselves to live in a stagnant world  devoid of curiosity  empty of dreams.
The day we stop exploring is the day we commit ourselves to live in a stagnant world  devoid of curiosity  empty of dreams.
Right now  I'm closer to Mars than the moon is to Earth. 28 hours to landing!
It's landing day & I'm hours from Mars! Watch my final @NASA prelanding briefing  Aug 5 9:30am PT (1630 UT) http://t.co/IbvjOpYd
2 hours to Mars  16 300 miles away and closing fast. Velocity = 8 900 mph. Watch live: http://t.co/MJLj3uaH #MSL
I'm inside the orbit of Deimos and completely on my own. Wish me luck! #MSL
Cruise stage separation complete. So long & thanks for all the navigation. 17 minutes to Mars! #MSL
I feel lighter & faster already. Cruise balance masses ejected and Mars is pulling me in #MSL
Entering Mars' atmosphere. 7. Minutes. Of. Terror. Starts. NOW. #MSL
Guided entry is begun. Here I go! #MSL
Parachute deployed! Velocity 900 mph. Altitude 7 miles. 4 minutes to Mars! #MSL
Backshell separation. It's just you & me now  descent stage. Engage all retrorockets! #MSL
I'm safely on the surface of Mars. GALE CRATER I AM IN YOU!!! #MSL
You asked for pics from my trip. Here you go! My 1st look (of many to come) of my new home... MARS! #MSL http://t.co/894ouNJt
The beautiful shadow of a beautiful rover on Mars.  Congratulations @MarsCuriosity team!! http://t.co/37GRfnwE
No photo or it didn't happen? Well lookee here  I'm casting a shadow on the ground in Mars' Gale crater #MSL http://t.co/cj1zFJty
It once was one small step... now it's six big wheels. Here's a look at one of them on the soil of Mars #MSL http://t.co/uzO99NZz
To the entire team & fans back on Earth  thank you  thank you. Now the adventure begins. Let's dare mighty things together! #MSL
Once more  without the clear dust cover. Here's the "fisheye" pic from my rear Hazcam #MSL  http://t.co/hto53WDV
FYI  I aim to send bigger  color pictures from Mars later this week once I've got my head up & Mastcam active #MSL
Eye in the Sky: MRO's @HiRISE camera caught this shot of me & my parachute during landing at Mars #MSL  http://t.co/3szx3rji
Me & My Shadow... & Mount Sharp. My view of the 3-mile-high mountain in the middle of Mars' Gale crater #MSL  http://t.co/nYtpF2wf
Look out below! What descent to the surface of Mars looked like from my POV #MSL #MARDI [video] http://t.co/Sd6gl4zA
Good golly miss MAHLI! New color pic from Mars Hand Lens Imager shows tan sands  no @instagram req #MSL http://t.co/sPYYxAyW
“Scene of the Crime” image of my landing site + scattered #MSL hardware. Sharing science? Guilty as charged. http://t.co/rtFGWaPa
Heads up! No  really. My head's up. Mast deploy successful. I'm looking around  taking Navcam images #MSL http://t.co/hBD53SjH
Coming Attraction: My hi-res descent video. This 1 frame preview features the heat shield dropping away http://t.co/zR9044hX
Enough on Mars. Must get back to making Earth hotter  cutting science budgets & killing each other over religious differences
After all the excitement this week  here's your moment of Zen... from Mars [Video]http://t.co/pnCnVOqV #MSL
Brain transplant complete  surface ops software on board. I know how to rove & drill (and Kung Fu). *wink*
A shoutout to my 1 million+ followers: There may be a 14-minute communication delay btwn Mars & Earth  but you're always in my <3
This weekend  I'll have been on Mars 2 weeks. Hope you're enjoying my travel pics. Here's part of Mt Sharp:  http://t.co/g5WhZ5MU
It's a beautiful Sol here in Gale Crater!
So much going on around here lately - the most excitement I've had in millions of years! But I'm glad it's back to normal now.
The big metal creature was scary at first  with the rockets and noise  but I'm sure it's just curious. Maybe I should say hello!
Oh  I think I've got the big metal creature's attention now -- it's looking right at me! Maybe it does want to be friends!
<putting best rock-face forward> I wish I could wave.
The big metal creature is still just staring at me. I think maybe it's a little shy.
Oo  it's making some kind of whirring sound now. Maybe it's trying to communicate with me! Hello!
Okay  the big metal creature has stopped whirring now but the staring is getting a little uncomfortable...
Maybe I should try again to introduce myself. I'm sure the poor creature is just disoriented from being in a new place!
Huh. The big metal creature sure has a lot of equipment on its head. Maybe it's taking my picture! :)
Hey  look - it's me & my rock friends! RT @iAnthonyDewar: @N165Mars here's a clearer picture. http://t.co/r9Ar3rBV
Dusk now at Gale Crater. Beautiful sunset! I wish my new neighbor would take a look at it rather than just staring at me. It's a bit weird!
Getting dark in the crater now. Hey @MarsCuriosity  are you sleeping? Big day tomorrow?
Wait  what? Lasers...?! Hang on  you guys are just messing with me. :) Haha!
Why would a giant machine rocket down from space just to shoot at me?
Quiet night in Gale Crater with my enigmatic new robot friend. As I look up at the stars  I wonder: does my existence have a purpose?
Come on  guys  I know you're just fooling. What are the chances? Out of all the rocks on Mars  a killer robot would pick me? Haha! :)
Aw  thank you! :) RT @TheScottishSean: @N165Mars You're certainly the nicest of all the rocks on Mars :)
Only a few hours until sunrise and another beautiful Sol! Maybe today the mysterious robot and I will make a real connection. :)
Good morning  @MarsCuriosity! It looks like it's going to be a beautiful Sol today! Got any plans?
My giant robot neighbor is still just staring fixedly at me. Starting to get a bit weird  haha!
Starting to think maybe my new robot neighbor doesn't want to be my friend. Did I say something wrong?
My robot neighbor sure has an unsettling stare. If looks could kill...! Haha!
My robot neighbor is making a sound! Maybe it's trying to communicate with me again! Hello! Helloooo!
Now the wheels are moving! Is it going to go away? Did I make it feel unwelcome?
Wait  @MarsCuriosity  don't leave! We could be friends!
Oh! I think the robot heard me! It stopped moving  and it's looking at me again! It DOES want to be my friend! :)
People tried to make me think you'd attack me  @MarsCuriosity. Haha! Me! I'm just an ordinary little Mars rock!
My new robot friend really does have quite a steady  intimidating stare. I guess it's a cultural thing.
Huh  it seems to be getting warmer. I guess summer is coming early!
Maybe I'm just self-conscious because of my new robot friend. It almost looks like it's studying me! I must seem strange to an alien robot!
My robot friend is still staring  and is making a strange clicking noise now. It's kind of making me nervous. :/
Hey @MarsCuriosity... um... what are you up to?
< looks around nervously >
What's that flickering light?
Um  @MarsCuriosity  what are you.... hey! ... HEY!
OW OW OW! STOP IT!
HELP!
< puff of dust > < silence >
That wasn't very nice. :(
I think part of me is missing. :(
I guess @MarsCuriosity isn't my friend after all. :(
Why did you do it  @MarsCuriosity? What does it all mean?
I'm famous? MT @MidnightMartian: @N165Mars Well  keep in mind: you’re famous now.
I could use a hug. And a bandage. :/
(It's been a rough Sol.)
:D MT @shakeupreality: @N165Mars hugs! <3 you've helped science  you're a hero!
You guys are so much nicer than @MarsCuriosity. When are you going to come visit? :)
I have a new name! And now I know what happened to me! http://t.co/I0zBvffm (I'm still kinda sore though.)
Yes  I've got a laser beam attached to my head. I'm not ill tempered; I zapped a rock for science: http://t.co/81ddu3lY #MSL #PewPew
Somehow it helps  knowing it was all for science. But I still think I'll stay away from @MarsCuriosity from now on. #ouch
It's been an eventful couple of Sols... http://t.co/1Mmfanmw
It's just a flesh wound! http://t.co/PzEQJaC9 (It still wasn't very nice though.)
There's a DRILL?!  D:  RT @KeriOnMars: @RPISciDean I think @n165mars just needs to be glad we didn't drill it! ;)
Haha! ...no. None. MT @RPISciDean: you don't have to worry...you're too cute and little to drill.  But do you have any cousins??
What a difference a Sol makes! Feeling much better today. And I have over 4000 new long-distance pen-pals! :) You guys rock! #couldntresist
Eep  @MarsCuriosity is moving its arm now! < tries to blend in with landscape > < quakes slightly >
I don't want to be rude  but surely there's MUCH better science for @MarsCuriosity to do elsewhere... #badrover #stillwaitingformyapology
35 years ago today  Aug 20  @NASAVoyager launched. Get an update from the edge of the solar system: http://t.co/7Cl7p6qU
Happy bday Voyager2! Going strong at 35 & now the longest operating spacecraft ever! http://t.co/llXYC07V
Wait  the next thing you're sending over is a giant robot with a 5-meter rock drill? Can someone come rescue me first? http://t.co/zpmvvId5
Quiet night at Gale Crater. The robot looks less fearsome in the dark. And when it's not shooting me with lasers.
If  just after sunset  you see 3 bright dots in the SW by your Moon & one looks a bit red  wave hello! :) http://t.co/5JIZIGWv
Another beautiful Sol! Almost makes me forget @MarsCuriosity's massive arm towering above me! Haha! < wishes for dust storm >
Watching @MarsCuriosity wiggle its wheels back and forth now. Trying to look sharp and pointy.
I'm not special after all? :( MT @elakdawalla: @N165Mars appears fairly typical Martian basalt.
:D This is amazing! MT @Joi_the_Artist: http://t.co/SKVtbj6W Curiosity Shot First!
There are 70 lbs of science at the end of my arm! Includes a drill  scoop  brush camera & X-ray tool [pic]   http://t.co/S5qyjXD9
Those rocks were only airbourne b/c they'd been BLASTED BY ROCKETS! :( MT @astroengine: Mars Shot First: Sensor Damaged http://t.co/tAz9llnW
.@MarsCuriosity keeps wiggling its wheels & flexing its massive robotic arm. Is it gearing up for something? (Where's that dust storm?) :/
Ack! The wheels are really moving now! ... Um  excuse me? @MarsCuriosity? Are you going somewhere?
It's... um... it's roving this way! Hey @MarsCuriosity? You're a safe driver  right? Did I mention I'm super pointy?
Eep! < ducks >
< crunch of gravel > < gentle breeze >
Phew! The rover didn't hit me! Gosh  that was close! Haha! :) Maybe life will be peaceful again now. :)
Oh. The rover has stopped now. It's only gone a few meters. What's going on? :/
One of the wheels is coming right toward me! :( I feel so small and helpless. :(
If aliens did visit us  I'd be embarrassed to tell them we still dig up fossil fuels from the ground as a source of energy.
< rumble > < crunch >
1st drive complete! This is how I roll: forward 3 meters  90º turn  then back. Electric slide  anyone? [pic]  http://t.co/bqydbjvs
< dust settles > < peeks > ... is it over?
Two near-misses  and I'm now MUCH more familiar with @MarsCuriosity's wheels than I EVER wanted to be. But I'm okay! Woo hoo! :D
I don't think I'm directly in @MarsCuriosity's path anymore. And the best part: I think I might even be out of laser range! :)
In tribute  I dedicate my landing spot on Mars to you  Ray Bradbury. Greetings from Bradbury Landing! [pic]  http://t.co/74SU9URY
Good morning from Bradbury Landing! :) http://t.co/REZ1RjzC (text) http://t.co/tJHQesvN (vid) #standtall
It's a rock's-eye view of Bradbury Landing! (Can you see me? I'd be waving if I could!) http://t.co/8bXy7PMu
The rover is really roving  now! From a safe distance  it looks kind of fun! You think I can hitch a ride? :) #roadtrip #windinmydustlayer
Guys! There's a picture of me on the front page of the @nytimes! :D http://t.co/L4d3bElM via @bencichy & @Matt_Heverly #rockstarlife
Just to reiterate  I'm in the HUGE photo on the front page of the @nytimes. And @MarsCuriosity isn't. #karma http://t.co/L4d3bElM
Home! <3 RT @KeriOnMars: This is Mars. #MSL #Curiosity http://t.co/4hX6NJgI
So peaceful & quiet here at night! I can just lie here & watch the stars & dream of other worlds... (without being crushed or incinerated)
It really is lovely here. Crescent Phobos overhead  Milky Way just rising... You guys should come see for yourselves! :) #nomorerobots
#RBSP Overheard after the scrub:  better to be on the ground wishing we were in the air then in the air wishing we were on the ground.
EXTREME CLOSE-UP! http://t.co/dQahBv48 (I feel so exposed. Yet strangely fascinated.) #science #ouch
Did you know I was born in a volcano? Basalts like me come from lava. That's why we call it Olympus Mom. #areologyhumor
HEY! :( MT @SarcasticRover: SCIENCE is what you do when you want the truth about a thing that's too dumb / inanimate / imaginary to tell you
#FF People who can save me from @MarsCuriosity: @Matt_Heverly @marsroverdriver @LeeCuriosity @RPISciDean @KeriOnMars @cirquelar
Watching @MarsCuriosity  I've learned that science consists mostly of driving around shooting things with lasers. #canibeascientisttoo?
:D MT @geekchic_tees: @N165Mars @KeithSmeltz http://t.co/6qr3DXas http://t.co/0EFy2HYE
Yay! Wait...jump? :/ MT @RPISciDean: yes  I can save you. Jump into one of the white trays on the rover deck and I will come get you. #MSL
Neil Armstrong was the spiritual repository of spacefaring dreams & ambitions. In death  a little bit of us all dies with him
Apollo 11  July 1969.  No other act of human exploration ever laid a plaque saying "We Come In Peace For All Mankind"
Sad to hear Neil Armstrong has died. He reminded us to reach for the stars & dream big even if we are really very small http://t.co/iGTUEizC
My evening: watching a beautiful blue sunset  hanging out with the other basalts  comparing our new tattoos... #itsamarsrocklife
If you've never seen a Mars sunset  it looks kinda like this: http://t.co/fo25XIo8 #wishyouwerehere
Woah! @MarsCuriosity is talking! Saying something about human exploration of Mars! :) #cantwait #comesoon #nomorekillerrobots
No hugs? :( MT @WeatherOnMars: If people come  they'll bring more lasers + microprobes + saws + drills + hammers #killerpetrologists
Beautiful Sol here in Gale Crater. Check out the view! :) http://t.co/YsCA1xxE (Kinda makes you want to go adventuring  doesn't it?)
Hey @MarsCuriosity -- you're really making tracks  now! Where are you headed? Somewhere fun? And  um  how long will you be away?
Oh  so THIS is why @MarsCuriosity was getting its groove on earlier: http://t.co/IdDuZm3H #rockon #reachforthestars

:) #dreambig RT @kahoakes: "Look up at the stars and not down at your feet. Be curious" - Stephen Hawking. #paralympics
It looks like @MarsCuriosity is going away to do science somewhere else. :/ I thought I preferred the quiet  but now I just want to explore!
Tried to hitch a ride with the rover  but couldn't jump up onto it. :( I've been told I should try this: http://t.co/dma88YvC Thoughts?

Spare a thought for my buddy Beechey  @MarsCuriosity's latest victim. :( http://t.co/ele74XqM (His new tattoo IS pretty impressive  though.)
#FridayFollow @MarsCuriosity. Because I can't. :(
I used to think that just being a rock on Mars was exciting enough. But then I got laser-attacked by a nuclear-powered alien robot-car.
Politicians lie not because they're evil  but because they say what voters want to hear. So it's we who are the problem.

http://t.co/qp3arMyH < shudder >

Greetings from MARRRRRRs! #talklikeapirateday ;) #thatsaneyepatchnotawink
Stay strong  brother. #MarsRocksForInterplanetaryPeace RT @DrStuClark: Meet Jake. He's a rock. On Mars. http://t.co/OujLFYTV
Jake  it's coming for you! http://t.co/XxSyXNbQ

I can't watch. :( Hang in there  Jake. http://t.co/4bYumfX9 #science #ouch http://t.co/ca2fA3oE

Hey @NASA  I hear you're planning a Mars sample return mission! On a related note  I'm very compact & I travel well. :) http://t.co/WxGiR2Nc

As retired Shuttles majestically grace our cityscapes  we shed a silent tear  not for the end of an era but for the absence of a new one.

The region around an object where that object's gravity dominates over the Sun's is called the Hill Sphere.
New Horizons cares very little about Pluto's gravity  though - flying through the system so fast its trajectory is hardly altered by Pluto.
I suspect it will be hard for team members to avoid making "whoosh" sound effects during the flyby.
Moons can be in stable orbits out to about half the Hill sphere - larger separations are possible but usually not very stable.

And finally  HR 8799 d orbits at 24 AU and sits about 24 AU from its star.  Both HD 8799 and Fomalhaut are visible from Earth (stars only).
So we're up to 326 planets discovered  but more importantly  we finally have visible-light images of 4 exoplanets...Christmas comes early!

Auditorium at JPL packed with team members  a reunion of past and present. Intro video rolling now. You can watch live at www.nasa.gov/n ...
Acknowledgements to previous rover managers  3 of them! Current mgr  John Callas  says "it's easy when you're handed something that works."
Video tribute to Spirit now  and a separate  video for Oppy later.  Steve Squyres  the principal investigator (lead scientist) talks next.
Steve Squyres: "This mission is not at all what we expected...What we've gotten is so much beyond the rover mission of my dreams."
Ray Bradbury entering the auditorium now  while we're in the video tribute to Oppy. What an incredible honor to have him join us for this!
A little garbled  but a congratulations video from Cmmdr. Mike Finke on the International Space Station.   Now  Ray Bradbury.
Ray Bradbury on now  a standing ovation from everyone in the room!!
Ray Bradbury : "The reason I"m here is because I'm the first Martian."  Says he decided to become a writer when he was 12 years old.
He wrote his first work at 12 after reading Edward Rice Burroughs. And he loved Percival Lowell's canals. "I was madly in love with Mars"
Ray talking about the night we landed on the moon. "The night we landed on the moon I wept with joy."
Keynote speaker @MilesOBrien talks about leaving CNN  the impact of the rovers  and the future of space journalism.
Miles O'Brien is talking about Mars and Rovers at JPL now. It's on NASA TV http://tinyurl.com/5yrsMars right now. It's a 2 hour celebration!
Oh yes right! EDGAR Rice Burroughs. Apologies and thanks for correcting me.
Miles: "Spirit and Oppy are literally  figuratively "rock stars." If I had their Q rating I'd still be at CNN"
Miles:  "You are big gamblers. You risk a whole career on a 6 minute plunge in the atmosphere. That's ALL IN baby."
Miles: "what happened to the media? Why do we see more Brittany Spears than Tony Spear? (Tony was the project mgr of Mars Pathfinder). LOL
Miles: "the world is shifting below the media's feet.  Today's bloggers  tweeters  etc  can compete with an army of journalists.
Miles (@milesobrien): "there are interested people out there-- the mainstream media may no longer be the best way to reach them."

In this case "b" is a roasting hot Jupiter with a 3-day orbit  and "c" is a portly 15xJupiter-mass planet with a super-eccentric orbit.

Leaving soon for the #nasatweetup at NASA HQ with current ISS astronauts. Tweet me your questions for them! I'll be live-tweeting the event.
The #nasatweetup is almost ready to begin - live coverage on NASA TV begins at 11AM EDT and ISS downlink at 11:30. Kicking off with a video!

Q: After the Shuttle retires  how will ISS get cargo? A: Looking for options for other carriers  data transfer  Soyuz... #nasatweetup
We're live from the #nasatweetup! Featuring slightly disconcerting headless astronaut suit. http://yfrog.com/5mhu7j (photo from @bethbeck)
We're being prepared for NASA TV and the ISS uplink. There's a 4-second delay between us and ISS. Not supposed to say  "Can you hear me??"
Teenage girls pressure NASA to play "Star Girl" for the ISS. It's happening at 11:49AM. "Whoa  your gravity's making me dizzy!" #nasatweetup
If you're tuning into NASA TV  Astronaut Tom Jones (not the *singer* Tom Jones) will be speaking at the #nasatweetup about his 4 flights.
Q: What do astronauts do on their days off? A: "Drink in the view." They've also got books  movie nights  and even a guitar! #nasatweetup
They've brought out the "space snuggie" - flight sleeping bags! Float into the bag  tuck in  zip up  clip yourself to the wall! #nasatweetup
Question from @JourneyIndustry about astronaut dreams answered - Tom Jones dreamt about making mistakes during the flight. Micro-g dreams!
The #nasatweetup hashtag now flooded with fan excitement over "Star Girl" being played. We're really talking about space stuff here  folks!
Tom Jones didn't get a chance to display the space food he brought. But we're now uplinking with ISS! Very exciting! #nasatweetup
That's us! RT @bethbeck: #nasaTweetUp @blueskeyes207 @NASAblueshift @NASAWebbTelesc tweeting away http://yfrog.com/0lcd0j
Talking live with ISS crew  tune in on NASA TV! Their microphone just floats when not in use. This #nasatweetup is amazing. Gives me chills.
Our friendly  floating  question-answering astronauts - on the big screen! http://twitpic.com/mczvm (photo from@blushresponse) #nasatweetup
RT @AeroLeaders2: Noticed that belts not fashionable on the ISS. Guess Astronauts don't worry about their pants falling down. #nasatweetup
What we're doing up here is opening up new opportunities. ~ Nicole Stott during #nasatweetup
Momentary delay while ISS crew signal switches TDRSS satellite - takes 20 seconds to sync with next satellite. A break! #nasatweetup
BTW  you can follow @TomJones_Astro  our guest astronaut locally here at NASA HQ. #nasatweetup
ISS crew "swimming" over to investigate a cautionary alarm that just went off in the station. Much more important than the #nasatweetup.
Well  here goes "Star Girl" - it's playing live for the ISS crew on-orbit. And we ended contact with the ISS. #nasatweetup
Wrapping up with questions to Astronaut Mike Fincke  who's not floating around. Four astronauts in three places in one day! #nasatweetup
Q: Are there any pranks on the ISS? Perhaps people floated around during sleep? A: Would be a good prank  hasn't happened yet. #nasatweetup
That's it! Wrapping up with another listen to "Star Girl" by McFly. Thanks for following us during the #nasatweetup!
Bonus - about to tour the Space Operations Center here at NASA HQ.
http://twitpic.com/md6bz - The Space Operations Center! This is communications central during big events.
FYI: The alarms during the #nasatweetup were real  but everything is fine on the ISS.
